content:
To incorporate a requirement for implementing the new policy within a specific time frame and rewrite the sentence in active voice using C++ code, consider the following:

Original Sentence (Passive):  
"The new policy must be implemented within a specific time frame."

Rewritten in Active Voice using C++ code:  
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <chrono>
#include <thread>

void implementPolicy(const std::string& policy, int timeFrameDays) {
    std::cout << "Implementing policy: " << policy << std::endl;
    std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::seconds(timeFrameDays * 86400)); // Simulating time frame in days
    std::cout << "Policy implemented within " << timeFrameDays << " days." << std::endl;
}

int main() {
    std::string policy = "New Policy";
    int timeFrameDays = 30; // Specify the time frame in days
    implementPolicy(policy, timeFrameDays);
    return 0;
}
```

In this code snippet, the function `implementPolicy` actively implements the policy within the specified time frame, simulating the process using a sleep function based on the number of days.
